[3] Media advisory: WHO/UN
Date: Fri 12 Jul 2019
Source: UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA), ReliefWeb [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/democratic-republic-congo/media-advisory-high-level-event-response-and-preparedness-ebola


What: High-level event on response and preparedness for the Ebola outbreak in the Democratic Republic of the Congo
Who:
- Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus, Director-General, WHO
- Mark Lowcock, UN Under-Secretary-General for Humanitarian Affairs and Emergency Relief Coordinator

On [15 Jul 2019], in Geneva, WHO Director-General, Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus, and UN Under-Secretary-General for Humanitarian Affairs and Emergency Relief Coordinator, Mark Lowcock, will convene a high-level Event on Response and Preparedness for the Ebola Outbreak in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).

Participants will include:
- H.E. Dr Oly Ilunga, Health Minister, DRC
- The Rt Hon Rory Stewart, Secretary of State for International Development, United Kingdom
- Mr David Gressly Emergency Ebola Response Coordinator ( by video from DRC), United Nations, among others [see full list of participants at the source URL above]

The meeting will provide an opportunity for the DRC Government, UN, NGOs, donors, and other partners to take stock of the status of the disease outbreak and response, and discuss the actions needed over the next 6 months. The discussion will include an update on the enhanced response put into place since May [2019], including the innovative tools being used, how past lessons have been applied, and the way forward. This will be an opportunity for the international community to re-affirm its commitment to support the response politically and financially to reach zero new Ebola cases.

